---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Admin's Choice collects, uses, and protects information, including third-party advertising and cookies."
  updated="June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Admin's Choice ("we", "us", or "the site")
    handles information when you visit <strong>adminschoice.com</strong>. We aim
    to collect as little personal data as possible while keeping the site useful
    and sustainable.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>
    Admin's Choice does not require you to create an account, and we do not ask
    for personal information to read our content. The information that may be
    collected falls into three categories:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information you provide.</strong> If you use our contact form, you
      voluntarily provide your name, email address, and message so that we can
      respond. We use this only to reply to your enquiry and do not sell it.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Automatically collected data.</strong> Like most websites, our
      hosting provider and analytics may record standard technical information
      such as your browser type, device, approximate region, and the pages you
      visit. This is used to understand traffic and improve the site.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cookies and similar technologies.</strong> See the
      <a href="/cookie-policy/">Cookie Policy</a> and the advertising section
      below.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising and third-party vendors</h2>
  <p>
    This site displays advertising to support its operation. Advertising is
    provided by one or more third-party advertising networks &mdash; currently
    including Google AdSense, and potentially others in future. The following
    applies to advertising on this site:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Third-party advertising vendors and their partners use cookies and similar
      technologies to serve and measure ads based on your prior visits to this
      and other websites.
    </li>
    <li>
      Where Google is used, Google's advertising cookies (including the
      DoubleClick cookie) enable Google and its partners to serve ads based on
      your visits to this site and/or other sites on the Internet.
    </li>
    <li>
      Each advertising network and partner collects information through its own
      cookies and technologies and processes it under its own privacy policy,
      over which we have no control.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What advertising cookies may collect</h3>
  <p>
    When advertising cookies are active, the data processed by advertising
    vendors and their partners may include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>your IP address and approximate location (country or region);</li>
    <li>device, browser, and operating system information;</li>
    <li>pages you view on this site and the time spent on them;</li>
    <li>your prior visits to this and other websites, used to personalise ads;</li>
    <li>interactions with ads, such as clicks and views.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
  <p>
    Some pages on this site contain affiliate links to third-party retailers and
    programs &mdash; currently including the Amazon Associates Program, and
    potentially others in future. If you click an affiliate link and make a
    purchase, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. This does
    not influence our recommendations.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Affiliate links may direct you to third-party sites that set their own
      cookies to attribute referrals and measure purchases. These cookies and
      any data they collect are governed by the third party's own privacy
      policy, over which we have no control.
    </li>
    <li>
      We do not receive your payment details, card information, or the specifics
      of what you purchase &mdash; only aggregated commission and referral
      reporting from the affiliate program.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Pages containing affiliate links carry a visible disclosure. See our
    <a href="/disclaimer/">Disclaimer</a> for more.
  </p>

  <h3>Consent for visitors in the EEA, UK, and Switzerland</h3>
  <p>
    If you are located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or
    Switzerland, we ask for your consent before any non-essential cookies &mdash;
    including advertising and analytics cookies set by us or by third parties
    &mdash; are stored on your device. When you first visit, a consent banner
    lets you accept or reject these cookies, and you can manage or withdraw your
    choices at any time using the privacy settings link in the page footer.
    Until you consent, non-essential cookies are not set, and where consent is
    declined, advertising vendors that support it serve only non-personalised
    ads, which use cookies solely for frequency capping, aggregated reporting,
    and fraud prevention.
  </p>
  <p>
    For advertising networks that require it (such as Google), consent is
    collected through a certified Consent Management Platform that supports the
    IAB Transparency &amp; Consent Framework, as required for serving ads to
    users in these regions.
  </p>

  <h3>Opting out</h3>
  <p>
    Regardless of location, you can manage personalised advertising at the
    industry opt-out pages, which cover many advertising vendors at once:
    <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>
    (US), and
    <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">youronlinechoices.eu</a>
    (EU). You can also opt out of individual vendors through their own privacy
    settings.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <p>We use the limited information we collect to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>respond to messages you send through the contact form;</li>
    <li>understand which content is useful and improve the site;</li>
    <li>maintain security and prevent abuse;</li>
    <li>display advertising that helps fund the site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. Information may be processed by
    service providers we rely on to operate the site (such as our hosting
    provider, contact-form processor, and advertising partners), strictly to
    provide those services.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights and choices</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or
    delete personal information we hold about you, and to object to certain
    processing. To exercise any of these, contact us via the
    <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. You can also control cookies through
    your browser settings and opt out of personalised advertising using the
    links above.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This site is intended for a technical, professional audience and is not
    directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
    information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be
    reflected by the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy can be sent through our
    <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
